# Prisma Models Overview

NeonDB Postgres with **11 active Prisma models** (post v0.7e Phase 5 cleanup S.254 ‚Äî `LinkedWallet` + `WatchAddress` + `ConversationLog` dropped 2026-05-22; plus `UserPreferences.contacts` column dropped same migration; plus prior v0.7d Phase 6 Block A drops of `UserMemory` + `UserFinancialProfile` 2026-05-21 S.221). Schema lives at `apps/web-v2/prisma/schema.prisma`. Generated client output is `apps/web-v2/lib/generated/prisma`.

## Model catalog

### Identity + preferences

| Model | What it stores | Owned by | Updated by |
|---|---|---|---|
| `User` | `id`, `suiAddress` (unique), `email` (unique, optional), `emailVerified` (mirrors Google OIDC `email_verified` claim ‚Äî written on first sign-in via `/api/user/status`), `displayName`, `timezoneOffset`, `tosAcceptedAt`, `username` (Audric Passport SuiNS handle) | Auth/login flow | `/api/user/status` upsert |
| `UserPreferences` | `limits` (JSON spend limits + permission preset + agent config) | User | `/api/user/preferences` |

### Engine / conversation (post v0.7e Persistent Chats ‚Äî S.247)

| Model | What it stores | Owned by | Updated by |
|---|---|---|---|
| `Chat` | Persistent chat threads (id, suiAddress FK, title, visibility, createdAt) | Chat persistence | `lib/audric/chat-persistence.ts` |
| `Message` | AI SDK v6 native `UIMessage` rows (chat-scoped); replaces the legacy `ConversationLog` chat-transcript role | Chat persistence | `lib/audric/chat-persistence.ts` |
| `Vote` | Per-message thumbs up/down (rating layer for fine-tune dataset) | Chat persistence | `lib/audric/chat-persistence.ts` |
| `SessionUsage` | Per-session token + cost rollup (drives session-cap billing gate) | Engine | `/api/chat` end-of-session |
| `TurnMetrics` | Per-turn metrics (Spec 1) ‚Äî latency, attemptId, modifiableFieldsTouched, pendingActionOutcome, writeToolDurationMs | Engine harness | `/api/chat` (chat-time row), inline resume flow (updateMany on attemptId) |

### Silent intelligence (`<financial_context>` + context layers)

| Model | What it stores | Owned by | Updated by |
|---|---|---|---|
| `UserFinancialContext` | Daily on-chain snapshot ‚Äî savings/wallet/debt/HF/APY/recent activity | Cron | 02:30 UTC `financial-context-snapshot` Vercel cron |
| `AdviceLog` | Recommendations the agent gave (last 30d rehydrated each turn) | Engine tool | `record_advice` tool (via `lib/audric/moat-context.ts`) |
| `PortfolioSnapshot` | Historical portfolio totals for timeline canvas | Cron | Daily `portfolio-snapshot` Vercel cron |

> **Long-term memory layer (web-v2 production):** lives in `@mysten-incubation/memwal` (Mysten vector memory) ‚Äî NOT in Prisma. See `lib/audric/memwal-prepare-step.ts` + `lib/audric/memwal-write-callback.ts`.

> **Deleted in v0.7d Phase 6 Block A (S.221, 2026-05-21):**
> - `UserFinancialProfile` ‚Äî Claude-inferred risk tolerance / goals / horizon. Replaced by MemWal `analyze()` which extracts these signals organically from chat.
> - `UserMemory` ‚Äî up to 50 episodic facts (Jaccard dedup'd) + `ChainFact` rows (source='chain'). Replaced by MemWal `recall()` + `analyze()`.

> **Deleted in v0.7e Phase 5 cleanup (S.254, 2026-05-22):**
> - `LinkedWallet` ‚Äî multi-wallet aggregated portfolio feature retired. Current zkLogin flow is single-wallet-per-Google-account by construction.
> - `WatchAddress` ‚Äî watch-only addresses feature retired (was tied to `assertOwnsOrWatched` auth helper which now collapses to `assertOwns`).
> - `ConversationLog` ‚Äî superseded by `Chat`/`Message`/`Vote` triple (S.247 AI SDK v6 native persistence). The legacy retention cron was deleted alongside the model.
> - `UserPreferences.contacts` column ‚Äî feature retired in S.243 (contacts no longer rendered or accepted).

### Audric Pay + Audric Finance

| Model | What it stores | Owned by | Updated by |
|---|---|---|---|
| `Payment` | Sent payments, payment links, invoices (status, amount, recipient) | Pay flows | `/api/payments/*` |

> **Removed in SPEC 17 (S.103, May 2026):** `SavingsGoal` model + 4 `savings_goal_*` engine tools + `/api/user/goals` routes + `GoalsPanel` UI + `openGoals` field on `UserFinancialContext`. The savings-goal layer wasn't producing observable agent behavior change. Track savings progress via `health_check` + `portfolio_overview` + `yield_summary`.

### Indexer / analytics

| Model | What it stores | Owned by | Updated by |
|---|---|---|---|
| `AppEvent` | App-side events the chain classifiers ingest (chip taps, sponsor failures, key flows) | App | Various event emitters |
| `ServicePurchase` | MPP service purchases via `pay_api` tool. **Note:** `pay_api` engine tool was deleted in S.245 (2026-05-22) per V07E_D_QUESTION_AUDITS D-2 reframe; no new rows written. Existing rows retained for the upcoming Audric Store SPEC which will reuse this table shape. | Engine tool (historical) | None currently ‚Äî `pay_api` removed |

## Where to write ‚Äî only here, never in a route

Database writes are concentrated by domain to make audits + migrations sane:

| Domain | Write site |
|---|---|
| User identity | `apps/web-v2/app/api/user/*` |
| Conversation (Chat/Message/Vote) | `apps/web-v2/lib/audric/chat-persistence.ts` |
| Telemetry (TurnMetrics) | Inline in `apps/web-v2/app/api/chat/route.ts` (post-v0.7e Phase 5: `harness-metrics.ts` helper was archived with apps/web; writes are inline now) |
| Cron snapshots | `apps/web-v2/lib/jobs/*.ts` + `apps/web-v2/app/api/cron/*` + `apps/web-v2/app/api/internal/*` |
| Pay flows | `apps/web-v2/app/api/payments/*` |
| Advice + memory hooks (engine-side) | `apps/web-v2/lib/audric/moat-context.ts` (`record_advice` consumer) + `lib/audric/memwal-write-callback.ts` (MemWal `analyze` post-turn) |

If you find yourself reaching for `prisma.X.create` in a new place, ask whether the existing write site can absorb it. Drift in write sites ‚Üí drift in invariants.

## Where to read ‚Äî go through helpers when one exists

| Read | Helper | Don't write `prisma.X.findMany` for this |
|---|---|---|
| Portfolio | `getPortfolio(address)` | See `audric-canonical-portfolio.mdc` |
| Activity feed | `getActivity(...)` | `lib/activity-data.ts` |
| Last 30d advice | `buildAdviceContext(userId)` | `lib/audric/moat-context.ts` |
| Long-term memory | `memwalClient.recall(query)` via `prepareStep` | `lib/audric/memwal-prepare-step.ts` |
| ~~Episodic memories~~ | `buildMemoryContext(memories)` ‚Äî DELETED in v0.7d Phase 6 Block A | replaced by MemWal recall |
| ~~Financial profile~~ | `buildProfileContext(profile)` ‚Äî DELETED | replaced by MemWal recall |

Direct reads in route handlers are fine for one-offs. Pattern is: helpers when the read appears in 2+ places.

## Migrations

```bash
pnpm --filter @audric/web-v2 prisma migrate dev --name <descriptive-name>
pnpm --filter @audric/web-v2 prisma generate
```

After migration:
- Update this rule's catalog if a new model landed.
- If the model is read by the engine, update `engine-context-assembly.mdc` too.
- Add a `@@index` for any column you'll filter on. Postgres without indexes scales badly.
- Production deploy runs `prisma migrate deploy` via the `postinstall` + `migrate` scripts in `apps/web-v2/package.json`.

## What's banned

```typescript
// ‚ùå Direct prisma in a React component (server component or otherwise)
// ‚Äî always go through an API route or server action.
import { prisma } from '@/lib/prisma';
export default async function Page() {
  const user = await prisma.user.findUnique({ where: { id } });
}

// ‚ùå Cross-domain writes (e.g. engine tool writing User table)
// ‚Äî engine tools write engine-owned models (AdviceLog) only.

// ‚ùå Silently dropping invariants
prisma.user.upsert({ where: { suiAddress }, ... });
// ‚Äî always check email-linkage first (see zklogin-passport-flow.mdc).
```

